<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Ref=
erring to your email below of December 9.</span></p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Are=
 you able to indicate the status of the undertaking of your independent inve=
stigations as proposed below.
</span></p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We h=
ave received 3 tender responses back from the reinstatement service provider=
s who attended site with Raffaella and myself late last year.</span></p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">As w=
e are all aware we have received these tender responses based on the scope o=
f works provided by ASURNZ and subsequently shared with all parties.</span><=
/p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Agr=
eement on the scope of works is paramount to claim progression. If we can mo=
ve to determine the agreed scope for claim related loss =E2=80=93 we can mov=
e quickly afterwards to provide the final outcome.</span></p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I l=
ook forward to an update on your independent enquiries.</span></p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Tha=
nk you very much.</span></p>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Reg=
ards,</span></p>
