nk you for the email below.</span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We c=
an confirm that testing can commence at 2pm on Friday October 17.</span><spa=
n lang=3D"EN-US"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We w=
ill test from sample sites as required to complete a full and thorough deter=
mination of any potential contamination, inclusive of all the areas which yo=
u have referred to below.</span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">You=
 may undertake your own independent testing at any stage; however, Tower wou=
ld only consider reimbursement for testing which is - a) claim related &amp;=
 b) testing which is outside of that which
 Tower will complete.<span class=3D"x_apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></=
span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I a=
m confident that the Tower Insurance testing will be transparent, quantified=
 by lab results, and adequate to provide comfort for all parties.</span><spa=
n lang=3D"EN-US"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nb=
sp;</span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"x_MsoNormal"><u><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">=
Clarified scope of testing as follows:</span></u><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span=
></p>
</div>
<ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1" style=3D"margin-top:0cm">
<li class=3D"x_MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-top:0cm; margin-bottom:0cm"=
><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">150mm diameter inspection p=
ortals cut in wall cavities of every room on the first floor at a height of 3=
00 mm of floor level and directly underneath
 the top plate.</span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span></li><li class=3D"x_MsoLis=
tParagraph" style=3D"margin-top:0cm; margin-bottom:0cm"><span lang=3D"EN-US"=
 style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Testing of the roof cavity at the soffit junctio=
n where potential contaminants may have risen through the wall cavity. Testi=
ng of the roof cavity
 at the apex where smoke may have accumulated.</span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></=
span></li><li class=3D"x_MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-top:0cm; margin-b=
ottom:0cm"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Testing of the un=
derside of the rear large upper deck.</span><span lang=3D"EN-US"></span></li=
><li class=3D"x_MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-top:0cm; margin-bottom:0cm=
"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Testing of the basement ut=
ilizing all exposed framing cavities and 150mm testing portals cut into any r=
emining ceiling linings in the basemen
